subject: Soccer
Olympic Games
lead_paragraph: Georgie Wilson Welcome beat goalkeeper Dominic Cervi in the 13th minute of overtime with a shot to the top-right corner of the net, and Honduras held on for a 1-0 victory against the United States in the Concacaf men’s Olympic qualifying tournament championship game in Nashville. Both teams had already clinched a berth in the Summer Games in Beijing. Earlier, Canada beat Guatemala for third place, 5-3 on penalty kicks after a scoreless regulation.
